Peseta debt / interbank market closing report . Spanish government bonds ended sharply higher on Wednesday but off peaks amid growing confidence Spain would meet the convergence criteria and join in the launch of the European single currency . Rumours about the worsening health of Russian president Boris Yeltsin , later denied , knocked the market off its peaks but it ended the day sharply higher nonetheless . " There are few reasons to explain in a logical fashion what ' s happening in the bond market , " one dealer said . There were hopes for further interest rate cuts in Spain after the Bank of Spain raised worries about consumer demand . 
